  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What are Lifecycle Hooks?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Lifecycle hooks are special methods in Vue that allow you to run code at specific stages of a component's life."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Lifecycle Phases"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Phase", "Hooks"],
        "rows": [
          ["Creation", "created"],
          ["Mounting", "beforeMount, mounted"],
          ["Updating", "beforeUpdate, updated"],
          ["Unmounting", "beforeUnmount, unmounted"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "created Hook"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Called when the component is created but not yet mounted to the DOM."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "created() {\n  console.log('Component created');\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "mounted Hook"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Called after the component is mounted to the DOM."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "mounted() {\n  console.log('Component mounted');\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "updated Hook"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Called when reactive data changes and the DOM updates."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "updated() {\n  console.log('Component updated');\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "unmounted Hook"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Called when the component is removed from the DOM."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "unmounted() {\n  console.log('Component destroyed');\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Use Cases"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Fetch data in mounted()**",
        "**Initialize variables in created()**",
        "**Watch DOM updates in updated()**",
        "**Cleanup resources in unmounted()**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Best Practices"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Use mounted for DOM-related logic**",
        "**Avoid heavy logic in updated**",
        "**Clean up timers and listeners in unmounted**",
        "**Use created for initial setup**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Common Mistakes"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Using DOM before mounted**",
        "**Heavy operations in updated hook**",
        "**Not cleaning resources in unmounted**",
        "**Confusing created and mounted hooks**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Conclusion"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Lifecycle hooks are essential for controlling component behavior at different stages, enabling efficient and organized Vue applications."
    }
  ],

  "faq": [
    {
      "question": "What is mounted?",
      "answer": "It runs after component is added to DOM."
    },
    {
      "question": "When to fetch API?",
      "answer": "In mounted hook."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is unmounted?",
      "answer": "It runs when component is removed."
    }
  ],

